-- Breaking Up Banks Would Be ‘Very Difficult,’ FSA’s Turner Says
-- B y   B e n   M o s h i n s k y
-- 2012-01-27T13:21:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-27/breaking-up-banks-would-be-very-difficult-fsa-s-turner-says.html
Breaking up some banks of the
largest banks to reduce the adverse affects of their failure
“would be very, very difficult,”  Adair Turner , the chairman of
the U.K. Financial Services Authority, said in a speech in
Davos,  Switzerland , today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
